                     <title xml:lang="en">A devotional poem (8ff) followed by passages selected from the Mathnawi.</title>
                     <note>On back cover: Book of Hindustani poetry - found in Goozerat 0n the 22nd of February 1849 - the day after the great action at that place E?D.E? Money. Inside front cover of the outer casing, pasted slip: Presented by E. Baverstock Esq to the Library of the Royal Asiatic Society through W?S? Arbuthnot. The first poem ends with a kind of dedication to a Muhammad Shah. Ruled margins.  Headings and some punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit (a): Chashm bigshay jilwah-i dildar Incipit (b): Hamd-i mahmudi kih dar jumlah suwar</incipit>
